des:
WOND takes pride in being Southern New Jersey’s LIVE and LOCAL source for the news and information that’s important to you. To get started, just say "Alexa, enable W. O.N. D. skill".

WOND is one of the legacy radio stations in Southern New Jersey. WOND signed on the air in July of 1950 licensed to Pleasantville, NJ with a variety format. The station evolved in the 1950’s from “Wonderful” music to a middle-of the-road format in the 1970’s before finally settling into its current role as the News-Talk leader in South Jersey in the 1980’s.
Today, WOND takes pride in being Southern New Jersey’s LIVE and LOCAL source for the news and information that’s important to you. WOND is where local listeners turn to find the forecast, traffic information and headlines that matter most in their lives. For decades WOND has been THE destination on South Jersey radio to get news and stimulating talk for listeners in both Atlantic and Cape May Counties.
